lexUnit.name: moan.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: a long, low sound, typically expressing grief

sentence.text: He gave the bad leg a gentle kick , to be rewarded with an agonized moan and the information that it was certainly broken , probably in two or three places .
And then he gave a small moan and the last vestiges of restraint were gone .
There were further moans and groans at the old toper 's repetition of an apparently well-worn story .
Zach gave a long ghostly moan and raised his hands .
He gave a loud moan and with a sudden retch , vomited all over the floor .
Her tolerance gave out and she uttered a moan and stamped her foot .
There was an angry moan as she did so and a pain in her chest , which made her wonder whether the moan had not been her own .
Not even the screams of the wounded and the moans of the dying broke the hush .
Wind noise , mainly , the gentle breeze from off the lough hissing in the trees , the occasional moan of distant engines .
The voice sounded faint and was soon drowned out by the rush and moan of the shells passing over .
The moan of a sax , earnest voices , the rumble of laughter .
Buildings were in flames and I could hear the screams and moans of the trapped and injured .
Loc let out a little moan of anguish .
They had all made that shrill moan during their funny parties , and by the time of Gary 's birth , Mary had come to recognise them for what they were -- satanic incantations .
He took a small mouthful from his plate then gripped at his stomach and emitted a low moan .
She moaned , a long , howling moan , but there was an ecstasy in the sigh that followed .
She made a little moan , her head refusing to obey her and tilting back in pleasure at the touch of his hands .
Maggie gave a low moan , her knees sagging , and he caught her close , turning her head to his shoulder , deepening the kiss and holding her against the length of his body .
She was about to turn around , when she heard a low moan .
There was a sudden hush , and then a low , wondrous moan rippled through the crowd .
But she did not answer him , only bent and lowered herself into the water , hissing as the coldness burned into the wound , a faint moan escaping through her gritted teeth as she began to wash .
